{
  "doc_id": "58624",
  "text": "We wanted to test if the promoter regions of the candidate genes show enrichment for the binding sites of the aforementioned ventral transcription factors, or for recognition motifs of TcfLef, the transcriptional effectors of canonical Wnt-signaling. Therefore, using the Transcription Element Search System (TESS) script [CITATION_1] we counted the number of such binding sites in the putative regulatory genomic regions of the analyzed genes. As transgenic reporter lines mimicking the expression of early transcribed developmental regulators often use 1-3 kb of the upstream genomic sequence [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , we decided to concentrate our efforts to the upstream 4 kb region.",
